						<p>Two detached fragments built into the shrine of the same temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Sundarapāṇḍyadēva: Year 13, Mithuna śu ••••• = 1264 A.D. (Jaṭāº Sundara-pāṇḍya-I?)</hi></p>						

						<p>These pieces are too fragmentary in nature. However, the record mentions a Vishṇu temple called Śendāmaraikkaṇṇaviṇṇagar ••• ••••• , and a village called Iḍaiyūr. </p>						

